Serbia Plans 1 Billion-Euro Shale Oil Joint Project, Blic Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-10-07T07:46:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/serbia-plans-1-billion-euro-shale-oil-joint-project-blic-says.html
Serbia will seek a partner for an
estimated 1 billion euro ($1.35 billion) investment to tap oil
shale reserves in the country,  Blic  newspaper reported, citing a
government official.  The government plans to own 51 percent of the future
venture whose operations should begin by 2016, near the southern
city of Aleksinac, the report quoted Deputy Mining Minister
Zlatko Dragosavljevic as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  